# ============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ============================================================================
# 1. CHANGE ALL PASSWORDS before deploying to production
# 2. Use environment variables instead of hardcoded credentials
# 3. Enable SSL/TLS for production databases
# 4. Restrict network access with firewall rules
# 5. Regularly rotate database passwords
# 6. Use secrets management tools (e.g., HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager)
# 7. Enable PostgreSQL audit logging
# 8. Set up regular automated backups

# ============================================================================
# URL ENCODING SPECIAL CHARACTERS
# ============================================================================
# If your password contains special characters, URL-encode them:
# @ → %40
# : → %3A
# / → %2F
# ? → %3F
# # → %23
# [ → %5B
# ] → %5D
# ! → %21
# $ → %24
# & → %26
# ' → %27
# ( → %28
# ) → %29
# * → %2A
# + → %2B
# , → %2C
# ; → %3B
# = → %3D

# Example with special characters:
# Password: MyP@ss!2025
# Encoded: MyP%40ss%212025
# URL: postgresql://user:MyP%40ss%212025@localhost:5432/database
